article.description: Trey Quartlebaum had 20 points as St. Francis (NY) routed Division III Medgar Evers 122-58 on Thursday night.
article.headline: St. Francis (NY) beats Medgar Evers 122-58
article.story: BROOKLYN HEIGHTS, N.Y. -- Trey Quartlebaum had 20 points as St. Francis (NY) routed Division III Medgar Evers 122-58 on Thursday night. Yaradyah Evans had 17 points and 13 rebounds for the Terriers (2-3). Chauncey Hawkins added 17 points. Stevan Krtinic had 14 points for the hosts. It was the first time this season the Terriers scored at least 100 points. Devin Berrios had 13 points for the Cougars. Isaiah Garvey-Mwazi added 11 points. Naquavah Jackson had 10 points and six rebounds. St. Francis (NY) plays Arkansas-Little Rock on the road on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
